  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification has been performed across key inlet boundary conditions and blood viscosity parameters, capturing aleatory variability in patient hematocrit (35–45%) and flow-rate tolerances (±5%). A future extension to include formal sensitivity analysis identifying dominant input drivers is planned but has not yet been executed.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-claim",
