      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form uncertainty is addressed qualitatively through turbulence model selection justification.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for internal rotating flows. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Qualitative justification documented. Factor not assessed per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (hematocrit, viscosity, inlet velocity profile) must be documented with sources and nominal values. Uncertainty quantification must be declared and propagated to QoI.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs are documented with literature sources. Hematocrit range 35–45%, dynamic viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s nominal. Uncertainty quantification has been performed using Monte Carlo sampling (500 runs) across inlet flow rate (±5%) and hematocrit variability, yielding a 95th-percentile NIH prediction band. The UQ results confirm that the nominal prediction remains below the RH < 1 threshold. We plan to extend this work with a formal sensitivity analysis to rank the dominant input drivers; however, that analysis has not yet been completed and no sensitivity analysis artifact is linked to this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
